</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="329" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,386,1880]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1482,1507]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Discussion.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blandford" box="[346,549,1482,1507]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" refString="Blandford, W. F. H. (1896) Scolytidae. In: Godman, F. D. &amp; Salvin, O. (Eds.), Biologia Centrali-Americana. Insecta, Coleoptera, 4 (6), pp. 81 - 144." type="journal article" year="1896">
Blandford (
<number box="[483,541,1482,1507]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" value="1896.0">1896</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[685,927,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hylastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipennis">
<emphasis box="[685,927,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Hylastes longipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from five specimens collected at Rancho Popocatepetl, 
<collectingCountry box="[310,399,1519,1544]" name="Mexico" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hagedorn" box="[411,604,1519,1544]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" refString="Hagedorn, M. (1910) Coleoptera Fam. Ipidae. In: Wytsman, P. (Ed.), Genera Insectorum, Fasc. 111. Brussels, pp. 1 - 178 + XIV plts." type="book chapter" year="1910">
Hagedorn (
<number box="[538,596,1520,1544]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" value="1910.0">1910</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Schedl" box="[661,819,1519,1544]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" refString="Schedl, K. E. (1940) Fauna Mexicana, 1. Insecta Coleoptera, superfamilia Scolytoidea: Scolytidae, Coptonotidae y Platypodidae Mexicanos. Anales de la Escuela Nacional de Ciencias Biologicas, 1 (3 - 4), 317 - 377." type="journal article" year="1940">
Schedl (
<number box="[753,811,1520,1544]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" value="1940.0">1940</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName box="[912,1078,1519,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hylastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipennis">
<emphasis box="[912,1078,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">H. longipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1258,1354,1519,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hylastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1258,1354,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Hylastes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wood" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" refString="Wood, S. L. (1982) The bark and ambrosia beetles of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae), a taxonomic monograph. Great Basin Naturalist Memoirs, 6, 1 - 1359." type="journal article" year="1982">
Wood (
<number box="[159,217,1557,1581]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
designated a female in Blandford’s series as the 
<typeStatus box="[792,894,1556,1581]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">lectotype</typeStatus>
and placed the species in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1319,1436,1556,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hylurgops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1319,1436,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Hylurgops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on its bilobed third tarsal segments and the intermixed large and small punctures on the pronotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,386,1880]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
The species distribution appears limited to that of the primary hosts, 
<taxonomicName box="[977,1112,1631,1656]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hartwegii">
<emphasis box="[977,1112,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">P. hartwegii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1169,1337,1633,1656]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montezumae">
<emphasis box="[1169,1337,1633,1656]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">P. montezumae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this could be a result of insufficient collections. These pines occur discontinuously at high elevations in the Trans- Mexican Volcanic Belt, the Sierra Madre de Oaxaca, the Sierra Madre de Chiapas, and in other smaller patches. The previously known distribution of the species showed it was restricted to the Trans-Mexican Volcanic Belt (
<bibRefCitation author="Atkinson" box="[158,582,1780,1805]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" refString="Atkinson, T. H. &amp; Equihua-Martinez, A. (1985 a) Lista comentada de los coleopteros Scolytidae y Platypodidae del Valle de Mexico. Folia Entomologica Mexicana, 65, 63 - 108." type="journal article" year="1985" yearSuffix="a">
Atkinson &amp; Equihua-Martínez 
<number box="[511,569,1780,1805]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" value="1985.0">1985</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Atkinson" box="[594,611,1780,1805]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" refString="Atkinson, T. H. &amp; Equihua-Martinez, A. (1985 b) Notes on biology and distribution of Mexican and Central American Scolytidae (Coleoptera). I. Hylesininae, Scolytinae except Cryphalini and Corthylini. The Coleopterists Bulletin, 39 (3), 227 - 238." type="journal article" year="1985" yearSuffix="b">b</bibRefCitation>
). New records from the 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[886,967,1781,1805]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">USNM</collectionCode>
collection expand the known distribution of this species, which seems to match that of 
<taxonomicName box="[655,789,1818,1843]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hartwegii">
<emphasis box="[655,789,1818,1843]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">P. hartwegii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as exemplified by its occurrence in a small population of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,285,1855,1880]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hartwegii">
<emphasis box="[151,285,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">P. hartwegii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Cerro Potosí, Nuevo León, in the Sierra Madre Oriental in 
<collectingCountry box="[1022,1111,1855,1880]" name="Mexico" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
